{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6f0c56f5-ecc6-46e1-91b5-bb8d3b11897d","content":"Your project is already set up. Run the tests in hot-reload mode with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a watch-style session that keeps the test host alive. When you edit your source or test files and save, it automatically re-runs the affected tests without a full rebuild — giving you a much faster feedback loop.\n\n**Tips:**\n\n- **Filter tests** to focus on failures:\n  ```bash\n  dotnet test --hotreload --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~EmailValidator\"\n  ```\n- Once running, just save your file edits and watch the console for updated results.\n- Press `Ctrl+C` to exit the session.\n\nThis is ideal for iterating on fixes since you skip the compile/restart overhead on each change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4f13d33d-a607-47a3-b9b9-66d10937579f","outputTokens":176,"requestId":"BC4C:926CA:1CB332E:200963D:69FA9803"},"id":"9a0242e1-cdf4-490a-925b-2820bae1751b","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:23:23.345Z","parentId":"1c8917a6-f4b4-4f27-8edd-2b42b9af8c5e"}
